CHANGE HISTORY ========================
Version 0.7 8/23/2007 - Added caTissue MolecularSpecimen to model, added association to Extract. - Brought caBIO Microarray into Logical Model, added association to ArrayDesign. - Cleaned up diagrams.
Version 0.6 8/21/2007 - Renamed Reporter to Probe in array package - Renamed CompositeReporter to LogicalProbe - Deleted sequence package -- reusing elements from caBIO - Revised sample package - Revised characteristics modeling - Created association from Sample to Specimen (from caTissue) - Organism from OrganismCDE model - Revised array package - Synched with concepts / model elements from caBIO
Version 0.5 8/21/2007 - Rolled back changes to BioMaterial characteristics to synch with current code and in anticipation of revision. - Fixed missing generalizations in model. - Added id:Long to data classes to ensure grid/caCORE compatibility. - Changed QuantitationType.type : Class -> type : String for grid compatibility - Changed CaArrayFile.status : FileStatus -> status : String
Version 0.4 8/12/2007 - Changed multiplicity Hybridization <--> DerivedArrayData - Added additional base class AbstractCaArrayObject (for objects that don't require LSID) - Revised DataSet and associated objects: added hybridization association to DataSet and made associations bidirectional.
Version 0.3 8/10/2007 [Model revision for review by Analysis Services Best Practices Working Group] - Put full array design annotation (Features, Reporters, etc.) back into the registered model. - Put hybridization data classes into the registered model.
Version 0.2 8/9/2007 - Added an association from Publication to Term to model the "type" of publication (main, reference etc.). - Added attributes to Publication based on MAGE-OM BibliographicReference (uri, publication, publisher, editor, year, volume, issue, pages). - Changed "Investigation" to "Experiment", and "InvestigationContact" to "ExperimentContact". - Changed multiplicity of Experiment's "factors" to 0..*. - Linked Experiment to Hybridization (many-to-many). - Added unit and value to FactorValue. - Allowed samples to have 0..* sources and extracts to have 0..* samples. - Removed LabeledExtract. Extract or Hybridization can have an associated label. - Extracts can be transformed into other Extracts (labeled or unlabeled). This satisfies ChIP-chip example shown in MAGE-TAB specification too. - Added amount and unit attributes to Hybridization. - Added association from RawArrayData to sourceImages (0..*). - Added a defaultValue for a Parameter. - Added a "notes" attribute to ProtocolApplication. - Added an association from Protocol to CaArrayFile to allow pdf description of protocol etc. - Expanded Characteristics into TermCharacteristics, ValueCharacteristics and well-known characteristics: Organism, OrganismPart, DiseaseState, DiseaseStaging and Age. - Searched caDSR and made list of potential reusable CDEs. Need to work with caDSR/EVS contact before annotating model. - Added a TODO item to add "documentation" tags for all classes and "description" tags for all attributes in order to make the model ready for submission to caDSR. - Added an ArrayGroup element.
Version 0.1 8/3/2007 - Initial draft reviewed internally. - Based on MAGE-TAB support with additional considerations for MIAME and caArray 1.x migration. - Result of E1 iteration.
